# Concern: CT/RT anchor inflexibility (midnight-only) + related overlaps

> **Raised:** 2026-04-23 after observing that the solver always places RT/CT
> rest days on midnight-to-midnight windows, regardless of surrounding shifts.
>
> **Status:** CURRENT STATE documented from fresh probe run
> (PLAN-20260423093611). FIX NOT YET IMPLEMENTED — design laid out below.
>
> **Hard requirement from the planner team:**
> - RT/CT must support **at minimum** three anchor offsets: **00:00, 12:00,
>   13:00**. The 12:00 and 13:00 cases are first-class; not edge-cases.
> - The scheduler must **never** place an RT/CT 24h window that overlaps
>   with the start or end of any demand shift on the same resource.
> - The solver must be smart enough to pick the anchor that keeps rest
>   compliance AND avoids overlaps — not just default to midnight.

---

## 1. Executive summary

**The solver allocates 100% of CT/RT rest days on calendar-day boundaries
(00:00 → 24:00 UTC), regardless of the surrounding demand schedule.** This
misses the legal and operational reality that a contiguous 24h rest can
start at any hour of the day. The midnight lock causes real overlap bugs
(rest days overlapping night-shift ends) AND blocks legitimate schedules
(can't sensibly rest a resource the same day they worked a night shift).

The requirement is a **discrete multi-anchor choice**: the solver should
pick, per (resource, day), one of a configurable set of anchor offsets
— minimum `{00, 12, 13}` — that best avoids overlap and respects all
hard constraints.

