## 8. Related: cross-partition CT×RT mutex leak (separate concern)

Orthogonal but nearby. The probe run also showed 1 CT×RT overlap
(res=290). This is from partitions solving the same (r, d) independently
and both emitting a rest-day row. `model.Add(rt[r,d] + ct[r,d] <= 1)` is
a WITHIN-partition constraint; across partitions, nothing prevents it.

Scope: 1 case in the 2-month probe. 490 cases in the full-fleet R7b run.
Separately concerning but not part of this fix.

Suggested separate concern document once Fix #17 lands — the carryover
mechanism introduced for rest-day windows could ALSO carry CT/RT "already
allocated this (r, d)" state and prevent the mutex leak. Two birds, one
stone, but scoping them separately keeps the change sets diff-able.

